<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="491" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1435,725,894]" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,797,822]" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from other genera in 
<taxonomicName box="[732,827,797,822]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmeciza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis box="[732,827,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade by plumage. Extensive bare crown of male and mostly unmarked black male and brown female plumages distinctive. Differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1084,1195,833,858]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Pyriglena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1195,833,858]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Pyriglena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in tail length and bill length proportions. Domed-shaped nest differs from nest of 
<taxonomicName box="[823,947,870,893]" class="Aves" family="Thamnophilidae" genus="Myrmeciza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="491" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[823,947,870,893]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="491">Myrmeciza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
..
</paragraph>
